			<p>
				A <span>structured cabling system</span> is a complete system of cabling and associated hardware, which provides a comprehensive telecommunications infrastructure. Structured cable networks (SCN) are the backbone of any modern telecommunication system. It’s a multipurpose information-carrying medium combining Local Area Networks, Telephony networks, Information Security systems, Video surveillance.
			</p>
