		<div class="col-md-12">
			<p>
				The structured cabling is a system that provides a very "structured" approach to the entire cabling system—a single-mixed media network that handles all information traffic like voice, data, video, and even big complex building management systems. In brief, it could be described as a system that comprises a set of transmission products, applied with engineering design rules that allow the user to apply voice, data, and signals in a manner that maximizes data rates.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="col-md-12">
			<p>
				Structured cabling divides the entire infrastructure into manageable blocks and then attempts to 
				integrate these blocks to produce the high-performance networks.
